net.hudup.core.client

Class Response

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.hudup.core.client.ProtocolParam
      • net.hudup.core.client.Response
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Response
extends ProtocolParam
    Response class represents result of Hudup services such as recommendation task, updating database, information retrieval. Response has many public variables for storing different results. Each response corresponds with a particular request (Request) class. Response uses JSON format as exchangeable means. Note, JSON (JavaScript Object Notation) is a human-read format used for interchange between many protocols, available at http://www.json.org.
    • In case of recommendation request, response is the list of recommended items returned from service layer. Exactly, response wraps the returned RatingVector of methods Recommender.estimate(...) and Recommender.recommend(...). The public variable vRating refers to such rating vector.
    • For update request, response is the output variable indicating whether or not update request is successful.
    • For retrieval request, response is the piece of information stored in Dataset or KBase. If information is stored in Dataset, response often wraps a returned Snapshot. Note, dataset includes essentially rating matrix, user profiles, item profiles and context information. Snapshot is defined as an image of piece of dataset and knowledge base (KBase) at certain time point.
    Both request (represented by Request class) and response (represented by Response class) extend directly protocol parameter specified by abstract class ProtocolParam and so they have a tight interaction.
    Version:
    10.0

    • Field Detail

      • attributeList

        public AttributeList attributeList
        Result as attribute list. Note, attribute list contains many attributes. Attribute represented by Attribute class indicates the data type, which is also a wrapper of data type. Profile is one of important data structures, like record of table in database, has a list of values. Each value belongs to a particular attribute. Profile uses attribute to specify its data types and so profile owns a reference to an attribute list. Please see AttributeList class for details about attribute list.

      • booleanResult

        public BooleanWrapper booleanResult
        Returned result is boolean value which wrapped as BooleanWrapper class.

      • dataConfig

        Result as configuration.

      • fId

        public Fetcher<java.lang.Integer> fId
        Fetcher of identifiers. Such identifiers can be of items or users. Fetcher is the interface for iterating each element of an associated collection.

      • fProfile

        public Fetcher<Profile> fProfile
        Fetcher to retrieves many profiles. Fetcher is the interface for iterating each element of an associated collection. Note, profile is one of important data structures, like record of table in database, has a list of values. Each value belongs to a particular attribute. Profile uses a attribute list to specify its data types. Every object can be modeled as profile to be stored in archive (file).

      • fRating

        public Fetcher<RatingVector> fRating
        Fetcher to retrieves many rating vectors. Fetcher is the interface for iterating each element of an associated collection. Note, rating vector represented RatingVector contains ratings. If rating vector is user rating vector, it contains all ratings of the same user on many items. If rating vector is item rating vector, it contains all ratings of many users on the same item.

      • nominalList

        public NominalList nominalList
        Result as nominal list. Nominal list is a list of many nominal (s), specified by NominalList. Nominal data indicates discrete and non-number data such as weekdays {Monday, Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, Friday, Saturday, Sunday}. Nominal data is called nominal, in brief, represented by Nominal class.

      • profile

        public Profile profile
        Result as profile. Note, profile is one of important data structures, like record of table in database, has a list of values. Each value belongs to a particular attribute. Profile uses a attribute list to specify its data types. Every object can be modeled as profile to be stored in archive (file).

      • recommendlet

        @Deprecated
public Recommendlet recommendlet
        Deprecated. 
        Result as recommendlet. Recommendlet represented by Recommendlet class is a service or a small graphic user interface (GUI) that allows users to see and interact with a list of recommended items. Recommendlet is now deprecated.

      • snapshot

        public Snapshot snapshot
        Result as snapshot. Snapshot is an image of dataset owned by Hudup server at current time point, stored in memory. Snapshot is represented by Snapshot class.

      • stringResult

        public java.lang.String stringResult
        Result as string.

      • vRating

        public RatingVector vRating
        Result as rating vector. Note, rating vector represented RatingVector contains ratings. If rating vector is user rating vector, it contains all ratings of the same user on many items. If rating vector is item rating vector, it contains all ratings of many users on the same item.

      • externalRecord

        public ExternalRecord externalRecord
        Result as external record. Note, external record represented by ExternalRecord class is a record (a row in table) which is stored in other database (different from the framework database). It is opposite to internal record represented by InternalRecord class which is a record stored in the framework database.

        public static Response createEmpty(int protocol)

      • parse

        public static Response parse(java.lang.String jsonText)
        Parsing (converting) the specified JSON text (text form of a request) into the response. JSON (JavaScript Object Notation) is a human-read format used for interchange between many protocols, available at http://www.json.org. In this framework, JSON is often used to represent a Java object as a text, which means that JSON text is converted into Java object and vice versa.
